HEADWORD: Urticaria
<hw>Ur`ti*ca"ri*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Urtica</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The nettle rash, a
disease characterized by a transient eruption of red pimples and of
wheals, accompanied with a burning or stinging sensation and with
itching; uredo.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

